<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Bars 1-4 (stanza A): Lighter 2-3 note RH, 3-note open LH — grief/sorrow
- Bars 5-8 (stanza A repeat): Slightly fuller RH (3 notes at peak), LH adds doubled root
- Bars 9-11 (bridge): Most chromatic motion (B°, F, C), chromatic descent F→E→D in LH
- Bars 12-16 (cadence): Am→G→C full close with stepwise voice leading

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 2→3: LH top note C4→C4 common tone through Dm7→Am
- Bridge (bar 11): Chromatic bass line F-E-D-F highlighting inner harmonic motion
- Bars 13-14: Contrary motion — melody descends (B-c-d-c-B) while LH ascends (G-D-B→A-E-C)
- Final cadence (bar 15): Dm→C→Dm→G→C, clear V-I with pedal G1→C1

TEXTURE ARC:
- Pickup + bars 1-4: Sparse (2+3 voice) opening, consonant, grief-tinged in Am/Dm territory
- Bars 5-8 repeat: Slightly fuller, adds 3rd voice in RH for the repeat
- Bridge (9-11): Busiest texture — 4 chord changes per bar, chromaticism (B°), descending bass
- Bars 12-14: Sustain Am→G→C — space opens up for solemn reflection
- Bar 15-16: Stepwise Dm-C-Dm-G then full I close, pedal cinches the root
-->
